-- Coutinho Would Prefer to Stay on as Head of BNDES, Veja Magazine Reports
-- B y   A n d r e   S o l i a n i   a n d   A d r i a n a   C h i a r i n i
-- 2010-11-05T19:00:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/coutinho-would-prefer-to-stay-on-as-head-of-bndes-veja-magazine-reports.html
Luciano Coutinho  would like to stay
on as president of Brazil’s state development bank after
President-elect  Dilma Rousseff  takes office Jan. 1, Veja
magazine reported on its  website .  Coutinho is among candidates being by considered Rousseff
for key positions in her Cabinet, the Sao Paulo-based magazine
reported without saying where it obtained the information.  Rousseff is likely to retain Finance Minister  Guido Mantega 
and central bank President  Henrique Meirelles  as requested by
President  Luiz Inacio Lula  da Silva, Veja said.  Fabio Kercher, an assistant to the bank’s presidency,
confirmed Coutinho’s comments when contacted by Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporters on this story:
 Andre  Soliani in Brasilia at 
 asoliani@bloomberg.net 
 Adriana Chiarini  in Rio de Janeiro at 
 achiarini4@bloomberg.net  